[SN]TITLE[SN]
Autism-friendly Christmas grotto opens in York

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An autism-friendly grotto has been set up in York to provide a relaxed environment to visit Father Christmas.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
14 December 2016 Last updated at 10:42 GMT
The grotto includes a multi-sensory room and is booked in 30-minute slots, meaning no stressful queuing is involved.
Kerrie Stephenson, whose son has the condition, said the layout allows children to "do what they want".
